Based on the detected ingredients, here are some recipe suggestions:

**Vegetarian Soup:**

* Use the broccoli, kale, cabbage, and carrots for a hearty and nutritious soup. Heat a tablespoon of olive oil in a large pan and sauté the vegetables until tender. Add four cups of vegetable broth, salt, and pepper to taste, and simmer for 20 minutes. Serve hot with a side of crusty bread.
**Roasted Fish with Lemon and Garlic:**

* Use the two types of fish and season them with salt, pepper, and paprika. Drizzle olive oil over a piece of aluminum foil and place the fish on it. Squeeze fresh lemon juice and sprinkle minced garlic on top, folding the foil to create packets. Bake at 400°F (200°C) for 10-12 minutes, and serve hot with roasted vegetables.
**Chicken Wing Stir-Fry:**

* Use the chicken wings and cut them into bite-sized pieces. In a wok or large pan, add a tablespoon of sesame oil and stir-fry the chicken until cooked through. Add sliced bell peppers, green onions, and a cup of your favorite stir-fry sauce. Stir-fry until the sauce thickens, then serve over rice or noodles.
